description:
&lt;p&gt;SO THIS IS WHERE REMARKABLE STARTS….&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ARE YOU INTERESTED IN ACUTE SURGERY?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE YOURSELF WORKING AS A SPECIALIST SURGICAL DIETITIAN WITHIN AN AWARD WINNING TEAM?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IF SO - WE ARE LOOKING FOR &lt;strong&gt;YOU&lt;/strong&gt; TO BE A PART OF OUR REMARKABLE TEAM&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Nutrition &amp; Dietetic Department is a large forward thinking department based across 2 acute hospital sites and is currently managed in 6 teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit to a Specialist Band 6 Acute Surgical dietitian post. The post holder will be based within the inpatient dietetic team based at Hull Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full competency led training and support package will be provided to ensure you can develop your knowledge and skills in acute surgery and digestive diseases, as well as opportunities to expand your knowledge and skills in other areas including parenteral nutrition and critical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have a varied caseload and will be working in established multi-disciplinary teams in both the inpatient and outpatient settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to support student dietitians on their placements as we are an established B and C Placement provider. You will also be able to develop and take part in staff teaching and support the team in audit and service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hull University Teaching Hospitals provide a comprehensive range of acute services from two hospital sites with an extended catchment population of 1.3 million people. The department has strong links with the Universities of Hull and York, Leeds Beckett University and with the British Dietetic Association.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be HCPC registered dietitians or due to obtain registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reasonably priced hospital accommodation and help towards the cost of relocation may also be available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hull is a great place to work, play, live and unwind. Applicants should note that all new appointments to Hull University Teaching Hospitals are subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probation period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Penny Kingston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leader / Gastro Dietitan&lt;/p&gt;
